New Documentary Film Previewed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- A preview of the documentary film "Great Turn Brought about with Songun Revolutionary Leadership" was held at the People's Palace of Culture on December 20 on the threshold of the 12th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army.
 The film comprehensively deals with the immortal leadership exploits Kim Jong Il has performed by turning the "Arduous March" into a cheerful and victorious march despite all sorts of difficulties and trials before the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film impressively tells that, tightly holding the arms of the revolution in hand already in the early period of his activities, Kim Jong Il has trained the KPA as an army of devotedly-defending the leader, an ideologically strong army and a matchless revolutionary one replete with the spirit of becoming human bullets and bombs, thereby bringing about a proud victory in the political and military confrontation with the U.S. imperialists and the KPA is performing labor achievements in socialist construction, too, paving a wide avenue for building a great prosperous powerful nation. It convinces the audience that his Songun revolutionary leadership serves as an all-powerful treasured sword to defend the red flag of socialism and vigorously advance Korean-style socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also shows Kim Jong Il visiting Jagang Province to let the revolutionary soldier spirit created by the People's Army prevail throughout the country and praised the fighting spirit displayed by the people in the province as the Kanggye Spirit. 
The film contains scenes showing him giving field guidance to factories, cooperative farms, sites of land realignment and construction to bring about a great revolutionary surge in all fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film has scenes proving that the Pyongyang meeting, the first of its kind in 55 years of division, provided by Kim Jong Il with his noble idea and will for reunification and a bold decision and the publication of the north-south joint declaration, its result was an historic event proving the validity of the independent Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were senior officials of the Party and the state, officials of commissions and ministries of the Cabinet and national institutions, officials of the Party and power bodies and working people's organizations and working people in Pyongyang.

South Korean Students against Troop Dispatch 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- An emergency meeting of the "National Group of New Chairmen of the General Student Councils in 2004" was reportedly held at Yonsei University on Dec. 17.
 At the meeting a declaration of the group for the retraction of the decision on troop dispatch to Iraq was adopted. The declaration denounced the south Korean authorities for deciding at "a meeting of ministers of unification, foreign affairs and security" held in Chongwadae to send 3,000 additional troops to Iraq and lay the "motion of troop dispatch" of this scale before the "National Assembly." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Demanding the "government" authorities totally withdraw the plan of troop dispatch, rejecting the U.S. unjustifiable pressure for troop dispatch and lending an ear to the people's voice at an early date, it set forth the following action program: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In case the "motion of troop dispatch" were carried through the "National Assembly", students would immediately launch into a hand-in-hand belt action in front of its building to show their will against troop dispatch. And they will go on a sit-down for an indefinite period and rise up in a joint action with all the people till the plan of troop dispatch is revoked. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The students will wage a movement for the defeat of those who supported the "motion" in the "election to the National Assembly" next year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the meeting, members of the group called a press conference.

Japan's Attempts to Conceal Its Crimes Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- The Japanese government authorities in 1950-1960 under a meticulous plan, decided to reply that all the detailed records of forcible drafting of Chinese by the Japanese imperialists during the Pacific War had been burnt and concealed them organizationally, engaging themselves in a political operation to evade the charge, according to a recently declassified document of the Japanese Foreign Ministry. 
 Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The successive governments of Japan feigned ignorance, keeping in secrecy most of the records of the past crimes committed by the Japanese imperialists against humanity, except some of them which were brought into the open. As facts show, it was not that there were no materials on the Japanese imperialists' anti-human crimes, but that they have all along concealed them. The newly published list of over 420,000 forcibly drafted Koreans, too, had been concealed by Japan as top secrecy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than half a century has passed since the defeat of the Japanese imperialists. But there is no change in their wrong stand and attitude toward their past crimes. Herein lie the shamelessness and craftiness peculiar to Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underlying Japan's wrong approach to the crimes committed by the Japanese imperialists against humanity is the impudent idea of looking down upon other nations, the idea that "the Yamato nation" may rule the Asians. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's wrong attitude toward its past crimes is based on the aggressive idea to repeat the history of crimes. It clearly shows that there is no change in its aggressive nature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is resorting to every conceivable ruse to cover up its past crimes without repentance. But it can never evade compensation for its grave crimes against human rights.

All Koreans Called Upon to Uphold Songun Politics 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- All the Koreans strongly support and uphold the great Songun politics as genuine patriotic politics for dignity, sovereignty, security and interests of the Korean nation, keenly realizing its patriotic nature and inexhaustible strength through their experiences, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 Songun politics is a principled and just policy for national independence and a noble treasured sword of patriotism as it helps creditably defend and guarantee the dignity, sovereignty, security and interests of the country and the nation from foreign aggression in reliance upon invincible revolutionary armed forces, a powerful military deterrent force, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sovereignty, independence and prosperity of the country and the nation are guaranteed by arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S., pursuant to its high-handed and unilateralist policy, has gone to a reckless extent in its high-handed and shameless arbitrary practices, even openly launching an armed invasion of sovereign states in utter disregard of international law and the protest of the world people in a bid to gratify its criminal greed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is now working desperately to provoke a new war for stifling the DPRK by military force, misjudging that its reckless policy of strength will work on the Korean peninsula, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Peace has been preserved on the Korean peninsula and the south Koreans have lived in peace so far in the sphere of self-defence provided by the Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The validity, attraction and vitality of the politics have already been proved in practice and they are illustrated with added clarity with each passing day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans should positively support Songun politics, a patriotic politics for the whole nation, and wage a resolute struggle against those forces challenging it and intensify the movement to achieve reconciliation, cooperation and independent reunification by the concerted efforts of the nation under the banner of Songun.

International Solidarity with Korean People 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- The international support to and solidarity with the Korean people in their just cause has been strengthened to an extent hither to unparalleled this year.
 According to data available, at least 1,730 solidarity functions have taken place this year in the DPRK and over 80 foreign countries under the sponsorship of international democratic organizations and organizations for peace against war and foreign organizations for friendship and solidarity with the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An international conference for ensuring peace on the Korean peninsula was held in Pyongyang in July under the co-sponsorship of international democratic organizations and the Korean Committee for Solidarity with the World People. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the International Association of Democratic Lawyers, the secretary general of the Afro-Asian People's Solidarity Organization, the executive secretary of the World Peace Council, the chairman of the World Federation of Democratic Youth, the chairwoman of the Women's International Democratic Federation and other delegates in their speeches expressed the belief that the Korean people and army under the Songun leadership of leader Kim Jong Il would emerge victorious in the present confrontation with the United States as they did in the last Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution of the international conference and letters to the UN secretary general and the U.S. Congress were adopted there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pyongyang International War Crimes Tribunal was held within the framework of the international conference. Laid before the tribunal by a joint international investigation group was an indictment which classified into 13 major categories the crimes committed by the United States on the Korean peninsula over the past one century or more such as the provocation of the Korean war, massacre of civilians in the wartime, barbarities of chemical and germ warfare, human right abuses in south Korea and nuclear crimes. And a stern judgement was passed on all the reactionary and inhuman policies and crimes of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the international conference staged a solidarity demonstration and held a solidarity rally, at which they unanimously adopted the Pyongyang manifesto of international democratic organizations and organizations for friendship and solidarity with the Korean people calling upon the world peaceloving people to wage an extensive protest movement against the U.S. hard-line policy to stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In September, many delegates of foreign organizations and figures visiting the DPRK held a joint meeting of organizations for friendship and solidarity with the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages and letters of solidarity were sent to Kim Jong Il on every occasion such as the 3rd anniversary of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and the June 25-July 27 month of anti-U.S. joint struggle by international organizations, organizations for peace against war and foreign organizations for friendship and solidarity with the Korean people, political and public figures and people of various social strata. And statements were published and rallies, demonstrations, international meetings, seminars, photo exhibitions, film shows and other solidarity functions were held by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A meeting of the executive committee of the World Peace Council held in Greece in November issued a communique supporting the Korean people in their just cause and a joint statement on the peace and reunification of the Korean peninsula in the name of international organizations and peace organizations of different countries.

GNP's Farce under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- The Grand National Party of south Korea reportedly held a rally in protest against the "unfair investigation into the presidential election funds", "attempts to disband the opposition party and conspiratorial politics" in front of the "National Assembly" building on Dec. 18.
 Choe Pyong Ryol cried out for a "special inspection of the presidential election funds", grumbling that the prosecution investigates the GNP only over the "illicit presidential election funds" while leaving the chief executive untouched. He noisily called for a thorough investigation into the suspected scandal of close associates of the chief executive, talking about the suspicious delivery of illicit funds to the former official of Chongwadae. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary dismisses this as the last-ditch effort of those who have no hope for the future as they are destined to go to ruin and another ridiculous political burlesque. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is none other than the corrupt GNP, a group of thieves and traitors which threatened, blackmailed and forced business groups to provide it with illegal presidential election funds amounting to over 60 billion won last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP is worse than Mafia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Pyong Ryol and his group should look back on their wrongdoings before faulting others and disclose the truth about all its illicit funds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Driven to a tight corner after the disclosure of its hideous financial scam, the GNP is now working desperately like a drowning man trying to catch a straw. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people have already passed a death sentence to the GNP. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Only a grave awaits Choe Pyong Ryol and his ilk.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Glorifying Songun Era 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- The DPRK will consolidate the political and ideological base of the revolution as an impregnable fortress and continue to glorify the era of Songun with the armed forces strong in idea and faith trained under the deep care of the great illustrious commander  Kim Jong Il who is pursuing the Songun policy as the main force, says Rodong Sinmun today in an editorial article.
 Noting that the army is a pillar and main force of the revolution the article says that a revolution means building up an army and vice versa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The might of the army is guaranteed by its servicemen's thinking and faith, the article says, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea and faith define the character and mission of the army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary army organized and guided by the idea of the leader truly serves the popular masses in accomplishing the cause of independence as the army of the leader and the party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army's will also depend on its idea and faith. What a high role an army can perform depends on its transparent will. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary army equipped with the immutable idea and faith of its leader, supreme commander can play the role as the vanguard defending the gains of the revolution and bringing about social changes, and as a strong champion of the people's interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If an army is to be true to the idea and faith, it should become a perfect personifier of the idea and faith. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 History and reality go to prove that the army strong in ideology and faith alone can preserve its class nature and creditably perform its role. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This army strong in ideology and faith means a mighty political force and a main force of the revolution pushing forward the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea and faith serve as a basic source enabling our army to become the main force of the revolution. Our revolutionary army is an army strong in ideology and faith, as it is equipped with the immutable Songun idea and faith of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This kind of army is built and glorified only by a great illustrious commander. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA has been trained as an army strong in ideology and faith as it has firmly established a system of revolutionary commandership and militant traits and all its servicepersons have formed a harmonious whole centering around the Supreme Commander. This is a brilliant result of the primary efforts our Party has consistently exerted for augmenting the political and ideological might of our revolutionary armed forces in its leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean revolution was pioneered and is making a victorious advance thanks to the army strong in ideology and faith. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our army regards the Songun idea and faith of Juche as its life and soul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun idea and faith of Juche means the idea and faith of    Kim Jong Il, the illustrious commander born of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our army has fully embodied the Songun idea and faith of Juche, demonstrating its invincibility. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The transparency of our army's Songun idea and faith of Juche is clearly proved by the revolutionary soldier spirit created and highly displayed among the servicepersons of the KPA under the leadership of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary soldier spirit is based on the spirit of devotedly defending the leader and carrying out his instructions and the heroic self-sacrificing spirit. This spirit means the revolutionary do-or-die, persevering and indomitable spirit. It is in this spirit that the soldiers of the KPA unhesitatingly devote their youth and lives to the Party and the leader, the motherland and the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our army is strong as it cherishes absolute loyalty to its supreme commander. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA soldiers' absolute loyalty to their supreme commander is the noblest revolutionary spirit displayed in the do-or-die struggle and the immutable thought and feelings manifested in their life and practice every moment. Our revolutionary practice shows that profound trust and love and absolute loyalty exist between the supreme commander and his fighters, who form an inseparable harmonious whole. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ours is a strong army in which revolutionary traits prevail as all its servicepersons act as one by an order of the supreme commander.
 The militant traits of the KPA are revolutionary ones established and consolidated with the transparent faith and will whereby it knows nothing but the orders and instructions of its leader, supreme commander. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The traits of the KPA mean the steel-strong discipline and order whereby all its servicepersons think and act as one according to the orders and instructions of its supreme commander. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our army remains a strong army because it devotedly carries out the orders and instructions of its supreme commander through thick and thin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA devotedly implements the orders and instructions of its supreme commander in practice under any circumstances, standing in the van of our revolutionary ranks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a sure guarantee for victoriously steering the era of Songun to give fuller display to the might of the idea and faith of the People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should vigorously make a long journey of the Songun revolution with the Songun idea and faith of the Party as guidelines in our life and struggle, single-heartedly upholding Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should model the whole society after the Songun idea and put the single-hearted unity of our revolutionary ranks on a new higher stage and effect a fresh surge in the socialist economic construction.

Celebration Meeting Held by Russian Public 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- A meeting of the Russian public was held in Moscow on Dec. 17 under the co-sponsorship of the Communist Parties-the Communist Party of the Soviet Union and the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK to celebrate the 12th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army and the 86th birth anniversary of Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese war hero.
 Kramarenko, a retired major general of the air force, in his speech said that the great feats of Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il lay in highly displaying the dignified sovereignty and international authority of the DPRK and turning the Korean People's Army into an invincible vanguard to defend socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that thanks to him, the great brilliant Songun commander, the DPRK is standing firm inspite of any moves of the United States and its followers to isolate and stifle it, he said victory and glory are always in store for the Korean People's Army and the people guided by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Writer Garifulina, member of the Council of the Communist Parties-the Communist Party of the Soviet Union, in her speech said: The life of Kim Jong Suk was a brilliant one that teaches what is the spirit of devotedly defending the leader and carrying through his instructions. She is a great pattern for the Korean people and the KPA officers and men in struggle and life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.

Revolutionary Sites Associated with Immortal Exploits of Kim Jong Suk
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- There are in North Hamgyong Province many revolutionary sites associated with exploits performed by anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.
 The Sonbong Revolutionary Site is a historical place visited by her in November Juche 34 (1945), upholding the policy of building a new country advanced by President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It includes the Sonbong Revolutionary Museum, monument to the Sonbong Revolutionary Site and the house where she stayed for work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At Sonbong Port, she made a speech calling upon wharf workers to unite as one and turn out in building a democratic, independent and sovereign nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chongam Revolutionary Site is located in Chongjin city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Haebang-dong lodging where she stayed, the house where she met officials, photo studio, etc. are preserved as they were in the revolutionary site. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the Haebang-dong lodging, she met her revolutionary comrades-in-arms and inspired them to work hard to implement the policy put forward by the President. On November 28, she met with reporters of the Saegil Sinmun newspaper and told them to explain the policy of building a new country advanced by the President so that the popular masses might take an active part in the efforts for its implementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Puryong and Kyongsong counties are also associated with her successful revolutionary activities. She met workers of the Puryong Metallurgical Factory and the Komusan Cement Factory to powerfully inspire them in the efforts for building a new country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are more than 330 places associated with her revolutionary activities in different parts of the country.

Stockbreeding Develops in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- The animal husbandry makes headway in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 This year the number of goats has increased over 43,000 and the acreage of grass lands some 12,000 hectares more than last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As compared with last year, the output of various kinds of milk products has increased 3.3 times this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chicken plants in the country including the Kanggye, North Phyongan Provincial, Hwangju chicken plants have kept the chicken and egg production on a high level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Mangyongdae Chicken Plant produces hundreds of thousands of eggs every month. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Tokchon Chicken Plant has overfulfilled the yearly chicken production plan by 130 percent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year's successes gained in the development of livestock breeding are closely linked with the wise leadership of  Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has given field guidance to a lot of goat breeding stations, goat farms, stockbreeding bases of co-op farms and chicken plants for the development of the country's livestock breeding. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In June alone he gave on-the-spot guidance to several goat breeding stations and farms to clearly indicate ways of boosting the livestock production considerably. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When he went to the Unjong Cooperative Stockbreeding Farm in North Hwanghae Province, he said that good species of goatlings should be bred extensively and the farm should be equipped with large and modern milk-processing facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When giving field guidance to the Kyenam Stockbreeding Farm in South Hwanghae Province, he gave tasks to build the farm in a far-sighted way and increase the production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also visited the newly built Hungju Chicken Plant and Kanggye Rabbit Breeding Station in July and August to give ways of attaining a high and steady rate of the meat, egg and processed milk production.
